# CCI Task/Flow Definition Rules

## Auto-Generated References

After editing `cumulusci.yml`, regenerate the CCI skill reference files:

```bash
python scripts/ai/generate_cci_reference.py
```

This updates `.cursor/skills/cci-orchestration/tasks-reference.md`,
`flows-reference.md`, and `feature-flags.md` from the current YAML.

## Task Naming
- `insert_qb_{plan}_data` or `insert_quantumbit_{plan}_data` — loads a data plan
- `delete_qb_{plan}_data` or `delete_quantumbit_{plan}_data` — deletes plan data
- `extract_qb_{plan}_data` — extracts from org
- `test_qb_{plan}_idempotency` — idempotency test
- `activate_{thing}` — runs an Apex activation script
- `deploy_*` — deploy metadata bundles
- `refresh_dt_*` — refresh decision tables
- `manage_*` — comprehensive management tasks (list, query, etc.)

## Required Fields
```yaml
tasks:
  my_task_name:
    group: Data Maintenance    # Required — groups tasks in cci task list
    description: >
      Specific description of what objects/SObjects are affected.
    class_path: tasks.rlm_sfdmu.LoadSFDMUData
    options:
      pathtoexportjson: datasets/sfdmu/qb/en-US/qb-pricing
```

## Task Groups

| Group | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `Revenue Lifecycle Management` | Core RLM tasks |
| `Data Maintenance` | Delete/reset data plans |
| `Data Management - Extract` | Extract data from org to CSV |
| `Data Management - Idempotency` | Idempotency tests |
| `UX Personalization` | Flexipage/layout/profile assembly |
| `E2E Testing` | Robot Framework UI tests |
| `Partner Relationship Management` | PRM-specific tasks |

## Feature Flags
- Defined under `project.custom` — boolean flags like `qb`, `billing`, `rating`, `rates`, `dro`, `ux`, `tso`
- Use `when:` conditions in flows to gate steps on feature flags
- `ux: true` enables `prepare_ux` (step 29). Set `false` to skip UX assembly.
- `tso: false` (default) — when `true`, selects TSO application variant

## `when:` Clause Syntax

```yaml
# Single flag
when: project_config.project__custom__billing

# Compound conditions
when: project_config.project__custom__dro and project_config.project__custom__qb

# Negation
when: not project_config.project__custom__refresh

# Scratch org detection
when: org_config.scratch and not project_config.project__custom__tso

# Complex conditions (quote to avoid YAML parsing issues)
when: "not (project_config.project__custom__quantumbit or project_config.project__custom__tso)"
```

## Flow Authoring

### Step numbering
Steps are integer keys. Use sequential numbers; gaps are allowed (Salesforce
convention) but avoid them for readability.

### Sub-flow nesting
Flows can call other flows or tasks:
```yaml
flows:
  my_flow:
    group: Revenue Lifecycle Management
    description: >
      What this flow does. Be specific.
    steps:
      1:
        flow: prepare_core        # call another flow
      2:
        task: deploy_full         # call a task
        when: project_config.project__custom__billing
      3:
        task: activate_records
        options:                  # override task options
          api_names: *some_anchor
```

### Adding steps to `prepare_rlm_org`
The main flow has strict ordering:
- Foundation (PSLs, PSGs, context defs) before metadata deploy
- Metadata deploy before data loading
- Products (PCM) before pricing/billing/tax/rating
- Rating before rates (FK dependency)
- UX assembly near the end (step 29) after all referenced components exist
- `stamp_git_commit` is always last

## YAML Anchor Patterns

This file uses YAML anchors extensively. Common patterns:

### Permission set lists
```yaml
project:
  custom:
    rlm_psl_api_names: &rlm_psl_api_names
      - BREDesigner
      - CorePricingDesignTime
      # ...

# Referenced in task options:
    options:
      api_names: *rlm_psl_api_names
```

### Decision table lists
```yaml
    dt_rating_decision_tables: &dt_rating_decision_tables
      - Asset_Rate_Card_Entry_Resolution_V2
      # ...

# Referenced in task options:
    options:
      developerNames: *dt_rating_decision_tables
```

### Dataset path anchors
```yaml
    quantumbit_pricing_dataset: &quantumbit_pricing_dataset "datasets/sfdmu/qb/en-US/qb-pricing"

# Referenced in task options:
    options:
      pathtoexportjson: *quantumbit_pricing_dataset
```

### Context definition anchors
```yaml
    sales_transaction_context_name: &sales_transaction_context_name RLM_SalesTransactionContext
    sales_transaction_context_default_mapping: &sales_transaction_context_default_mapping QuoteEntitiesMapping
    sales_transaction_context_base_reference: &sales_transaction_context_base_reference SalesTransactionContext__stdctx
```

### Sleep duration
```yaml
    sleep_default: &sleep_default 30
```

## `org_config.scratch` Usage

Use `org_config.scratch` in `when:` clauses to differentiate scratch org
vs persistent (sandbox/prod) behavior:
```yaml
when: org_config.scratch and not project_config.project__custom__tso
```

## Description Accuracy
- Don't list excluded objects in task descriptions
- Be specific about which SObjects are loaded/deleted/extracted
- For deploy tasks, mention what metadata types are included
